{"id":18,"parent_id":0,"book_id":80,"content_id":1,"language_id":1,"display_order":18,"title":"Chapter 15: Alma Teaches and Baptizes","subtitle":"","short_title":"Chapter 15","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-15-alma-teaches-and-baptizes","content":[["div",{"id":"container","role":"main"},["div",{"type":"chapter","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-15-alma-teaches-and-baptizes"},[".heading",{"id":"head1","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-15-alma-teaches-and-baptizes.head1"},[".titleNumber","Chapter 15"],["h1","Alma Teaches and Baptizes"]],[".bodyBlock",[".image",{"id":"f1","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-15-alma-teaches-and-baptizes.f1"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_018_01.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p3","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-15-alma-teaches-and-baptizes.p3"},"Alma escaped from King Noah’s servants and hid for many days. While he was hiding, he wrote down what the prophet Abinadi had taught."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p4","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-15-alma-teaches-and-baptizes.p4"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/17.3-4"},"Mosiah 17:3–4"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f2","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-15-alma-teaches-and-baptizes.f2"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_018_02.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p5","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-15-alma-teaches-and-baptizes.p5"},"Alma repented of his sins and went to the Nephites secretly, teaching them Abinadi’s message. Alma told the people to have faith in Jesus Christ and repent."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p6","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-15-alma-teaches-and-baptizes.p6"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/18.1,7"},"Mosiah 18:1, 7"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f3","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-15-alma-teaches-and-baptizes.f3"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_018_03.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p7","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-15-alma-teaches-and-baptizes.p7"},"During the day Alma hid in a pocket of trees near a pool called the Waters of Mormon."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p8","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-15-alma-teaches-and-baptizes.p8"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/18.5"},"Mosiah 18:5"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f4","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-15-alma-teaches-and-baptizes.f4"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_018_04.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p9","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-15-alma-teaches-and-baptizes.p9"},"Those who believed Alma’s teachings went to the Waters of Mormon and were baptized. Alma baptized 204 people into the Church of Christ."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p10","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-15-alma-teaches-and-baptizes.p10"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/18.8-10,16-17"},"Mosiah 18:8–10, 16–17"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f5","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-15-alma-teaches-and-baptizes.f5"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_018_05.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p11","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-15-alma-teaches-and-baptizes.p11"},"Alma ordained priests to teach the people. He told the priests to teach repentance and faith in Jesus Christ. He also said they must not argue but be united."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p12","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-15-alma-teaches-and-baptizes.p12"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/18.18,20-21"},"Mosiah 18:18, 20–21"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f6","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-15-alma-teaches-and-baptizes.f6"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_018_06.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p13","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-15-alma-teaches-and-baptizes.p13"},"Alma’s people loved and served one another. They shared everything they had and were grateful to have learned about Jesus Christ, their Redeemer."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p14","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-15-alma-teaches-and-baptizes.p14"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/18.29-30"},"Mosiah 18:29–30"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f7","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-15-alma-teaches-and-baptizes.f7"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_018_07.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p15","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-15-alma-teaches-and-baptizes.p15"},"King Noah’s servants saw Alma teaching the people. The king said Alma was turning the Nephites against him, so he sent an army to kill them."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p16","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-15-alma-teaches-and-baptizes.p16"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/18.32-33"},"Mosiah 18:32–33"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f8","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-15-alma-teaches-and-baptizes.f8"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_018_08.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p17","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-15-alma-teaches-and-baptizes.p17"},"God warned Alma that King Noah’s army was coming. The people gathered their families, animals, and other belongings and fled into the wilderness."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p18","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-15-alma-teaches-and-baptizes.p18"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/18.34"},"Mosiah 18:34"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/23.1"},"Mosiah 23:1"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f9","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-15-alma-teaches-and-baptizes.f9"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_018_09.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p19","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-15-alma-teaches-and-baptizes.p19"},"God strengthened Alma’s people so they could escape from King Noah’s army. The army searched but never found them."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p20","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-15-alma-teaches-and-baptizes.p20"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/19.1"},"Mosiah 19:1"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/23.2"},"Mosiah 23:2"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f10","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-15-alma-teaches-and-baptizes.f10"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_018_10.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p21","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-15-alma-teaches-and-baptizes.p21"},"After traveling in the wilderness for eight days, Alma’s people came to a beautiful area that had pure water flowing through it. Here they planted crops and built buildings."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p22","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-15-alma-teaches-and-baptizes.p22"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/23.3-5"},"Mosiah 23:3–5"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f11","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-15-alma-teaches-and-baptizes.f11"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_018_11.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p23","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-15-alma-teaches-and-baptizes.p23"},"The people wanted Alma to be their king, but Alma said God did not want them to have a king. God wanted them to be free."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p24","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-15-alma-teaches-and-baptizes.p24"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/23.6-7,13"},"Mosiah 23:6–7, 13"]]]]]]]],"refs":null}
